<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="443" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,439,573]" pageId="3" pageNumber="443">
<materialsCitation country="Brazil" location="Within" municipality="Sericothripinae" pageId="3" pageNumber="443" specimenCount="1">
There are 112 species listed in this Thripidae-Sericothripinae. The 
<typeStatus box="[922,970,439,465]" pageId="3" pageNumber="443">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName authority="John" authorityName="John" authorityYear="1929" box="[1077,1338,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Neohydatothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latereostriatus">
<emphasis box="[1077,1275,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="443">N. latereostriatus</emphasis>
John
</taxonomicName>
was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[299,370,475,501]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="443">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, but other members of the genus are found widely around the world. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:9F6E982C9564FFA7FF36FE9DFEBBD81A:12187FE19564FFA7FBCEFE28FB03DBD2" box="[1135,1212,475,501]" country="Brazil" municipality="Sericothripinae" name="Within" pageId="3" pageNumber="443">Within</location>
the 
<collectingMunicipality box="[1258,1432,475,501]" pageId="3" pageNumber="443">Sericothripinae</collectingMunicipality>
, members of this genus can be recognized by the metasternum connected in the middle with a T-shaped or Y-shaped apodeme
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
